msgid "SYNOPSIS: Installing multiple autotool versions in parallel."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: origin/autotools-multiversion.txt:16
msgid ""
"DESCRIPTION: GNU's autotools comprises of three packages: * autoconf: "
"<http://www.gnu.org/gnu/autoconf/> * automake: "
"<http://www.gnu.org/gnu/automake/> * libtool: "
"<http://www.gnu.org/gnu/libtool/> Details on how to use these packages can "
"be found at their homepage. Also refer to the autotools hint."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: origin/autotools-multiversion.txt:38
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"There are some misconceptions in the LFS community regarding "
"autotools. Before\n"
"going into the installation details, we will first tackle these\n"
"misconceptions.\n"
"* Misconception: Autotools are a \"core\" part of a system.\n"
"  Counter argument: These tools are useless for most of the LFSers. They "
"are\n"
"  only useful for folks who are maintaining an autotools based package.\n"
"  Someone compiling a package from source only needs autotools if they have "
"a\n"
"  patch that requires the package to be re-autoconfed. Currently there is "
"a\n"
"  grand total of 4 packages in BLFS and 0 packages in LFS that need "
"autotools.\n"
"  And perhaps, that requirement can be removed if a patch is generated "
"that\n"
"  patches the final files instead of the .in or .am files.\n"
"* Misconception: I only need the latest version of the tools.\n"
"  Counter argument: The various versions of autotools are not compatible "
"with\n"
"  each other. That is why all the distributions install multiple versions "
"of\n"
"  these packages in parallel. The various autotool versions are more like\n"
"  glib-1.x and glib-2.x series. If a package needs glib-1.x branch, you "
"cannot\n"
"  just expect it to work with glib-2.x branch. The distributions install "
"the\n"
"  following versions of packages:\n"
"  - autoconf: 2.13 2.59\n"
"  - automake: 1.4-p6 1.5 1.6.3 1.7.9 1.8.5 1.9.6\n"
"  - libtool: 1.5.20\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: origin/autotools-multiversion.txt:42
msgid ""
"This hint details a way to install these multiple versions in parallel and "
"allow you to choose which version to use. The general way to only install "
"versions that you need, when you need it."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: origin/autotools-multiversion.txt:51
msgid ""
"ATTACHMENTS: * "
"http://www.linuxfromscratch.org/hints/downloads/attachments/autotools-multiversion/autoconf-wrapper "
"* "
"http://www.linuxfromscratch.org/hints/downloads/attachments/autotools-multiversion/automake-wrapper "
"(Note: The following patches are optional but recommended)  * "
"http://www.linuxfromscratch.org/patches/downloads/autoconf/autoconf-2.13-race.patch "
"* "
"http://www.linuxfromscratch.org/patches/downloads/autoconf/autoconf-2.13-fedora_macro_fixes-1.patch "
"* "
"http://www.linuxfromscratch.org/patches/downloads/automake/automake-1.4-p6-fedora_fixes.patch "
"* "
"http://www.linuxfromscratch.org/patches/downloads/automake/automake-1.5-fedora_fixes.patch"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: origin/autotools-multiversion.txt:54
msgid "PREREQUISITES: None."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: origin/autotools-multiversion.txt:56
msgid "HINT:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: origin/autotools-multiversion.txt:61
msgid ""
"The multiple versions will be installed by making use of the "
"--program-suffix argument to the configure script. Then a wrapper script is "
"installed that will use the appropriate version based on the value of an "
"envar. If no variable is declared, the latest version is used."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: origin/autotools-multiversion.txt:68
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"* Installation of autoconf-2.13:\n"
"    patch -Np1 -i ../autoconf-2.13-race.patch\n"
"    patch -Np1 -i ../autoconf-2.13-fedora_macro_fixes-1.patch\n"
"    ./configure --prefix=/usr --program-suffix=-2.13\n"
"    make acdatadir=/usr/share/autoconf-2.13\n"
"    make acdatadir=/usr/share/autoconf-2.13 install\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: origin/autotools-multiversion.txt:73
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"* Installation of autoconf-2.59:\n"
"    ./configure --prefix=/usr --program-suffix=-2.59\n"
"    make pkgdatadir=/usr/share/autoconf-2.59\n"
"    make pkgdatadir=/usr/share/autoconf-2.59 install\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: origin/autotools-multiversion.txt:80
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"* Installation of automake-1.4-p6:\n"
"    patch -Np1 -i ../automake-1.4-p6-fedora_fixes.patch\n"
"    ./configure --prefix=/usr --program-suffix=-1.4\n"
"    make\n"
"    make install\n"
"    rm -v -f /usr/bin/*-1.4-1.4\n"
msgstr ""

